				<td colspan="2"><span>The other thing here is that this issue exists will all songs, not just selo's.  I refer to it as the precision bug and here is why:  If you refresh a song at the exact same time that it would be ending you get the text that the song was refreshed, but you do not get the effect or icon for the song.
<br />

<br />
I have a feeling that this exists in the buff stacking code since this has always been a problem and the only class that needs to refresh buffs with extreme frequency are Bards.  This issue annoys me the most because IRL I am a classicaly trained singer and have a good sense of timing as well I can type at about 120 mistakes a minute.  This combination makes playing a bard some what easier on me, but frusterating because I can be extremely precise in my twisting and Sony has this filthy bug that detriments my ability.
<br />

<br />
As for kiting and some conspiracy at Sony they don't actually support kiting, just as they don't support multiquesting.  In fact we are very lucky because kiting could be construed as exploitation, but so many people do it that Sony would be stupid to make any attempts to put an end to it due to the number of customers they would lose.</span></td>
